  "prompt": "What does the Chinese word \u300c\u6c14\u8d28\u300dmean?",
  "response": "The Chinese word \u300c\u6c14\u8d28\u300d (q\u00eczh\u00ec) can be translated as \"temperament,\" \"aura,\" or \"demeanor\" in English. It refers to a person's unique combination of personality, character, and overall presence, which makes them stand out. It encompasses one's inner qualities and how they are outwardly expressed, such as through behavior, speech, and appearance. \u300c\u6c14\u8d28\u300d is often used to describe someone who has a refined, elegant, or charismatic presence. It\u2019s a concept that emphasizes both the internal and external aspects of a person\u2019s personality.",
